  </read_first>
  <action>
  Apply the plan-02-03/02-04 transform to each of the 5 upper subtrees. MUST PROCESS IN THIS ORDER (dependency-lowest-first):

  1. `forge_services` (only up-deps on forge_app + forge_domain + forge_stream — all complete)
  2. `forge_infra` (up-deps on forge_app + forge_config + forge_domain + forge_fs + forge_select + forge_walker — all complete)
  3. `forge_repo` (up-deps add forge_infra — complete after step 2 of this task)
  4. `forge_api` (up-deps add forge_repo + forge_services — complete after steps 1-3)
  5. `forge_main` (up-deps on nearly everything — must be LAST)

  For EACH subtree run:

  ```bash
  SUBTREE=<NAME>
  SUBDIR=crates/kay-core/src/$SUBTREE

  # Rule 1a: non-grouped use crate::X;
  files=$(grep -rlE '^use crate::' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe "s{^use crate::(?!forge_)(?!\{)}{use crate::$SUBTREE::}g"
  fi

  # Rule 1b: grouped use crate::{...};
  files=$(grep -rlE '^use crate::\{' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe "s{^use crate::\{}{use crate::$SUBTREE::{}g"
  fi

  # Rule 2: inter-subtree
  files=$(grep -rlE '^use forge_[a-z_]+::' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe 's{^use (forge_[a-z_]+::)}{use crate::$1}g'
  fi

  # pub use variants
  files=$(grep -rlE '^pub use crate::' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe "s{^pub use crate::(?!forge_)(?!\{)}{pub use crate::$SUBTREE::}g"
  fi
  files=$(grep -rlE '^pub use crate::\{' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe "s{^pub use crate::\{}{pub use crate::$SUBTREE::{}g"
  fi
  files=$(grep -rlE '^pub use forge_[a-z_]+::' "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null || true)
  if [ -n "$files" ]; then
    echo "$files" | xargs perl -i -pe 's{^pub use (forge_[a-z_]+::)}{pub use crate::$1}g'
  fi

  # Verify invariants
  remain=$(grep -rhE "^(pub )?use crate::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null \
    | grep -v "use crate::$SUBTREE" \
    | grep -v "use crate::forge_" \
    | wc -l | tr -d ' ')
  legacy=$(grep -rhE "^(pub )?use forge_[a-z_]+::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')
  if [ "$remain" != "0" ] || [ "$legacy" != "0" ]; then
    echo "FAIL $SUBTREE: remain=$remain legacy=$legacy (first 30 lines):"
    grep -rhE "^(pub )?use crate::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null | grep -v "use crate::$SUBTREE" | grep -v "use crate::forge_" | head -15
    grep -rhE "^(pub )?use forge_[a-z_]+::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null | head -15
    exit 1
  fi

  # For forge_main / forge_api, also handle the bare inter-subtree path expression
  # form `forge_domain::ChatRequest` (not starting with `use`). This is rare but
  # check with grep; these usually appear in function bodies as qualified paths.
  # Skip if count is 0.
  bare=$(grep -rhE "[^:[:alnum:]_]forge_[a-z_]+::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null | grep -v "crate::forge_" | wc -l | tr -d ' ')
  if [ "$bare" != "0" ] && [ "$SUBTREE" = "forge_main" -o "$SUBTREE" = "forge_api" ]; then
    echo "NOTICE $SUBTREE: $bare bare path expressions referencing forge_X::... remain. Inspect manually:"
    grep -rhE "[^:[:alnum:]_]forge_[a-z_]+::" "$SUBDIR" 2>/dev/null | grep -v "crate::forge_" | head -10
    # These are qualified path expressions like `forge_domain::Foo::bar()` that
    # need rewriting to `crate::forge_domain::Foo::bar()`. If ANY are found,
    # abort this task and surface to human reviewer — bare path rewrites are
    # tricker than import rewrites and hand-edits are safer.
    exit 1
  fi

  git add -A crates/kay-core/src/$SUBTREE
  git commit -s -m "refactor(02-05): path-rewrite $SUBTREE

D-01 Step 2 final wave. Rewrites intra + inter imports in $SUBTREE.
Depends on all preceding plan-02-03/04 subtrees being complete.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>"
  ```

  After all 5 subtrees, assert kay-core actually compiles clean:

  ```bash
  cargo check -p kay-core 2>&1 | tee /tmp/02-05-final-check.out
  # Must exit 0 — if not, diagnose before Task 2
  cargo check -p kay-core --tests 2>&1 | tee -a /tmp/02-05-final-check.out
  # Also required — the imported tests must compile
  cargo check --workspace 2>&1 | tee -a /tmp/02-05-final-check.out
  # Must pass without --exclude
  ```

  If `cargo check -p kay-core` or `cargo check --workspace` still fails after the 5 commits land, DO NOT proceed to Task 2. Inspect the error list; common causes:
  - A few-liner pattern the perl rules missed (`pub(crate) use` for example) — rerun with wider regex
  - A `mod foo;` declaration pointing at a file that does not exist post-rename — this shouldn't happen because we never renamed anything other than lib.rs→mod.rs, but verify
  - A macro that emits `crate::X` inside `macro_rules!` — those expansions resolve at USE site, not definition site; inspect and adjust where used

  Fix, re-verify, and append fix-up commits under `refactor(02-05): fix-up $SUBTREE` names before proceeding to Task 2.
  </action>
